The paper discusses the importance of information visualization and social collaboration in academic digital libraries, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. Specifically, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.DL (Digital Libraries) are the most relevant sub-categories as they directly relate to the topic of the paper. Additionally, cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are also relevant as they discuss the user interface and social collaboration aspects of the digital libraries. Finally, cs.CL (Computation and Language) may also be relevant as the paper discusses the organization and interpretation of scientific documents, which may involve natural language processing techniques.
